abstract: College Roundup; Big 12 interim commissioner Chuck Neinas says Missouri will play in league for 2012-2013 season, giving the university time to decide whether to stay in the league or attempt to join the Southeastern Conference; other new noted.
snippet: The Big 12’s interim commissioner said that it was difficult to gauge whether to remain at 10 teams if Missouri stays or expand to 12 if it leaves for the SEC.
lead_paragraph: The Big 12’s interim commissioner said that it was difficult to gauge whether to remain at 10 teams if Missouri stays or expand to 12 if it leaves for the SEC.

headline.main: Missouri to Play in the Big 12 Next Season, and Then Decide
